An '''update site''' is a website that extends ImageJ's capabilities. With update sites, you do not need to manually download and install anything; Fiji takes care of it for you.

You can add support for an update site using the Help > Update Fiji command (or Help > Update in the case of ImageJ2) and clicking the "Advanced mode" button. For further details, see [[How to follow a 3rd party update site]].

Anyone can create their own update site; see [[How to set up and populate an update site]] for instructions. See notes below the table how to add your update site to the ''Manage update sites''' dialog.

